  {
    "id": 47571183,
    "title": "Show HN: CLI to order groceries via reverse-engineered REWE API (Haskell)",
    "url": "https://github.com/yannick-cw/korb",
    "score": 191,
    "by": "wazHFsRy",
    "time": 1774853158,
    "descendants": 80,
    "text": "I just had the best time learning about the REWE (German supermarket chain) API, how they use mTLS and what the workflows are. Also `mitmproxy2swagger`[1] is a great tool to create OpenAPI spec automatically.<p>And then 2026 feels like the perfect time writing Haskell. The code is handwritten, but whenever I got stuck with the build system or was just not getting the types right, I could fall back to ask AI to unblock me. It was never that smooth before.<p>Finally the best side projects are the ones you actually use and this one will be used for all my future grocery shopping.<p>[1]<a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;alufers&#x2F;mitmproxy2swagger\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;alufers&#x2F;mitmproxy2swagger</a>",
    "fetched_at": "2026-04-02T14:09:24.243670",
